gomodel:SYNGO_3992  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 4 B-D shows in rat cultured cortical neurons RTN3 is colocalized with Synaptophysin at DIV 11.\n\nFigure 1 demonstrates the specificity of the anti-RTN3 antibody using Western Blot. Two bands around 30 kDa were detected in the mouse brain with anti-RTN3 serum (PMID:11990451). Bands of 25kDa and 27kDa were detected in the rat retina (lane 1) and olfactory bulb (lane 3). Both of these bands were competed for more than 99% by N14 peptide (Lane 2 & 4).. Experimental description: Adult Sprague-Dawley rats were used in the study" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" ;
        dc:date           "2020-09-16" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3992" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

